Introducing Packages:
----------
package com.debesh.example;

public classs Main {
    public static void main(String[] args){

    }
}
----------
- Packages provide oraganization
- Follow standard naming
- Affect source code file structure
----------
Package Naming Conventions:
- All lowercase
- Use reversed domain name to assure global uniqueness 
Ex:
http://pluralsight.com
package com.pluralsight;
- Add further qualifiers to assure uniqueness within a company/group
Ex:
package com.pluralsight.myproject;
package com.pluralsight.accounting.myproject;
package com.pluralsight.coursemgmt.myproject;
---------
Members become part of the Package:
-
package com.pluralsight.myproject;

public class Main {
    public static void main(Strings[] args){

    }
}
-
com.pluralsight.myproject.Main 
--------
package name and source file structure:
- Java requires no correlation between package names and soure code file structure 
- But most IDE's require a sub-folder for each part of the package name 
Ex:
Main.java 
-
package com.pluralsight.example;

public classs Main {
    public static void main(String[] args){

    }
}
-
src -> com -> pluralsight -> example -> Main.java 